[109.372324, "o", "              urlscan.io     AS16509\r\n  asn                         urlscan.io     AS40034\r\n  asn                         urlscan.io     AS43350\r\n\r\n  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n  inframap | defang all IOCs before sharing | use responsibly\r\n\r\n\r\n  PHISHING KIT DETECTION\r\n  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n  Score: 100/100  Status: KIT DETECTED\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  IOC LIVENESS\r\n  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n  LIVE: 30  DEAD: 0  UNKNOWN: 0\r\n\r\n  LIVE\r\n  ● araujofa[.]onmicrosoft[.]co              HTTP 429 (355ms)\r\n  ● onmicrosoft[.]co                         HTTP 429 (312ms)\r\n  ● actopantortillas[.]onmicrosoft[.]co      HTTP 429 (425ms)\r\n  ● access[.]trzcianka[.]onmicrosoft[.]co    HTTP 429 (338ms)\r\n  ● anyconnect[.]trzcianka[.]onmicrosoft[.]co HTTP 429 (435ms)\r\n  ● anywhere[.]trzcianka[.]onmicrosoft[.]co  HTTP 429 (417ms)\r\n  ● apps[.]trzcianka[.]onmicrosoft[.]co      HTTP 429 (456ms)\r\n  ● 1lynden[.]mail[.]onmicrosoft[.]co        HTTP 429 (441ms)\r\n  ● akwrc[.]onmicrosoft[.]co                 HTTP 429 (431ms)\r\n  ● autodiscover[.]rosefinancial0[.]onmicrosoft[.]co HTTP 429 (447ms)\r\n\r\n\r\n  THREATFOX / URLHAUS MATCHES\r\n  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n  Checked 4 IOCs — no matches found\r\n  No matches found. ThreatFox/URLhaus track malware delivery URLs and \r\n  C2 endpoints. Infrastructure domains may not appear even when \r\n  confirmed malicious — this is expected behaviour. \r\n\r\n\r\n  CONFIDENCE SCORE BREAKDOWN\r\n  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n  Total: 95/100 — CONFIRMED\r\n\r\n  SIGNALS DETECTED:\r\n  + 25  Phishing infrastructure score\r\n       Multiple phishing kit signals detected simultaneously\r\n  + 20  VirusTotal malicious verdict\r\n       Multiple AV/security vendors independently flag as malicious\r\n  + 20  Certificate fast-spin\r\n       ≥5 TLS certs issued in one month = rapid infrastructure standup, not normal business\r\n  + 15  Cert issuance cluster\r\n       Multiple certs issued in the same short window by the same issuer\r\n  + 15  urlscan.io scan history\r\n       High scan count = active security community flagging\r\n  + 10  Wildcard SAN certificate\r\n       *.domain.com cert covers unlimited subdomains — common in phishing platforms\r\n  + 10  Infrastructure currently live\r\n       IOCs are actively responding — infrastructure is operational\r\n\r\n  WHAT WOULD INCREASE THE SCORE:\r\n  +30 if threatfox ioc match detected\r\n  +25 if abuseipdb high score detected\r\n  +20 if bulletproof asn detected\r\n\r\n\r\n  [ATT&CK] T1583 — Acquire Infrastructure (Resource Development)\r\n  [ATT&CK] T1583 — Acquire Infrastructure (Resource Development)\r\n  [ATT&CK] T1566 — Phishing (Initial Access)\r\n  [ATT&CK] T1056 — Input Capture (Credential Access)\r\n\r\n"]
